Initial Data Exploration

Documentation:

  • https://www.yelp.com/dataset/documentation/main

From the documentation the files include the following:

  • business.json - Contains business data including location data, attributes, and categories
  • review.json - Contains full review text data including the user_id that wrote the review and the business_id the review is written for.
  • user.json - User data including the user's friend mapping and all the metadata associated with the user.
  • checkin.json - Checkins on a business.
  • tip.json - Tips written by a user on a business. Tips are shorter than reviews and tend to convey quick suggestions.

Looking at the Review Text

Function to process text:

In[31]:
def preprocess_text(text):
    # Lowercase and remove non-alphanumeric characters
    text = text.lower()
    text = re.sub(r'[^\w\s]', '', text)

    # Remove punctuation
    text = text.translate(str.maketrans('', '', string.punctuation))

    # Tokenization
    tokens = word_tokenize(text)

    # Remove stopwords
    stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
    tokens = [word for word in tokens if word not in stop_words]

    # Lemmatizing
    lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
    tokens = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(token) for token in tokens]

    # Rejoin tokens into a single string
    processed_text = ' '.join(tokens)

    return processed_text
In[35]:
def preprocess_text_with_bigrams(text):
    # Lowercase and remove non-alphanumeric characters
    text = text.lower()
    text = re.sub(r'[^\w\s]', '', text)

    # Remove punctuation
    text = text.translate(str.maketrans('', '', string.punctuation))

    # Tokenization
    tokens = word_tokenize(text)

    # Remove stopwords
    stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
    filtered_tokens = [word for word in tokens if word not in stop_words]

    # Lemmatizing
    lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
    lemmatized_tokens = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(token) for token in filtered_tokens]

    # Generate bigrams and convert bigrams to a single string
    bigram_tokens = [' '.join(bigram) for bigram in bigrams(lemmatized_tokens)]

    # Combine unigrams and bigrams
    all_tokens = lemmatized_tokens + bigram_tokens

    # Rejoin tokens into a single string
    processed_text = ' '.join(all_tokens)

    return processed_text
In[36]:
def preprocess_text_just_bigrams(text):
    # Normalize text: lowercase and remove non-alphanumeric characters
    text = re.sub(r'[^\w\s]', '', text.lower())

    # Tokenization
    tokens = word_tokenize(text)

    # Remove stopwords
    stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
    filtered_tokens = [word for word in tokens if word not in stop_words]

    # Lemmatizing
    lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
    lemmatized_tokens = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(token) for token in filtered_tokens]

    # Generate bigrams
    bigram_tokens = [' '.join(bigram) for bigram in bigrams(lemmatized_tokens)]

    # Rejoin bigram tokens into a single string
    processed_text = ' '.join(bigram_tokens)

    return processed_text

# Function to tokenize and count words in a single partition
def count_words(partition):
    # Tokenize, handle NaN values by replacing them with an empty string
    tokens = partition['text_cleaned'].fillna('').str.split()
    # Flatten the list of lists to a single list of tokens
    flat_list = [item for sublist in tokens.tolist() for item in sublist if item]  # Ensure non-empty items
    # Count occurrences
    counts = {}
    for word in flat_list:
        if word in counts:
            counts[word] += 1
        else:
            counts[word] = 1
    return pd.Series(counts, name='count')

# Load data into a Dask DataFrame
ddf = dd.from_pandas(review_df, npartitions=10)

# Define the metadata as a Series of integers
meta = pd.Series(dtype=int)

# Apply the counting function to each partition
word_series = ddf.map_partitions(count_words, meta=meta)

# Convert series of dictionaries to a DataFrame and perform groupby sum
word_counts_df = word_series.to_frame(name='count')
grouped_word_counts = word_counts_df.groupby(word_counts_df.index).sum()

final_word_counts = grouped_word_counts.compute()

wordcloud = WordCloud(width=1200, height=600, background_color='white').generate_from_frequencies(final_word_counts['count'].to_dict())

plt.figure(figsize=(15, 9))
plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')

# Function to tokenize and count bigrams in a single partition
def count_bigrams(partition):
    # Handle NaN values by replacing them with an empty string
    bigrams = partition['text_cleaned_bigrams'].fillna('').str.split()
    # Flatten the list of lists to a single list of bigrams
    flat_list = [item for sublist in bigrams.tolist() for item in sublist if item]  # Ensure non-empty items
    # Count occurrences
    counts = {}
    for bigram in flat_list:
        if bigram in counts:
            counts[bigram] += 1
        else:
            counts[bigram] = 1
    return pd.Series(counts, name='count')
